286
00:15:52,584 --> 00:15:55,109
condemning the United States
government

287
00:15:55,187 --> 00:15:58,748
for promoting democracy abroad
while neglecting the rights

288
00:15:58,824 --> 00:16:01,725
of its African American
citizens at home.

289
00:16:03,796 --> 00:16:06,287
ROBESON: In attacking me,
they suggested

290
00:16:06,365 --> 00:16:08,026
that when I was abroad,
I spoke out

291
00:16:08,100 --> 00:16:11,399
against injustices to the Negro
people in the United States.

292
00:16:11,470 --> 00:16:12,937
I certainly did.

293
00:16:16,642 --> 00:16:20,009
GATES: Paul Robeson sought to
plead the cause of the Negro

294
00:16:20,079 --> 00:16:23,048
right here,
at the United Nations.

295
00:16:23,115 --> 00:16:25,709
In 1951, he presented a petition

296
00:16:25,784 --> 00:16:28,617
