after a year of protest,

381
00:21:49,408 --> 00:21:52,502
Montgomery finally
ended segregation

382
00:21:52,577 --> 00:21:54,340
on its city buses.

383
00:21:54,413 --> 00:21:55,744
Do you believe
the majority

384
00:21:55,814 --> 00:21:57,076
of the Negro people
of Montgomery

385
00:21:57,149 --> 00:21:59,982
will now go back
to riding the buses?

386
00:22:00,052 --> 00:22:02,953
Yes, I do.
We must go back

387
00:22:03,021 --> 00:22:06,548
with a deep sense of
love and dedication

388
00:22:06,625 --> 00:22:09,651
to the principle
of nonviolence.

389
00:22:09,728 --> 00:22:13,892
GATES: King's philosophy
of nonviolent civil disobedience

390
00:22:13,965 --> 00:22:16,934
was inspired by the principles
and practices

391
00:22:17,002 --> 00:22:19,903
of India's Mahatma Gandhi.

392
00:22:19,971 --> 00:22:23,998
The tactic was intended to
agitate segregationists,

393
00:22:24,076 --> 00:22:26,271
provoking a reaction
that would elicit

394
00:22:26,345 --> 00:22:28,336
widespread sympathy
from the public.

395
00:22:29,548 --> 00:22:32,381
